==English==

===Etymology===
{{suffix|absolute|ly|lang=en}}, from {{etyl|enm|en}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/æb.səˈluːt.li/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˌæb.səˈlut.li/|/ˈæb.səˌlut.li/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-absolutely.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Adverb===
{{en-adv|-}}

# In an absolute or [[unconditional]] manner; [[utterly]], [[positively]], [[wholly]]. {{defdate|First attested around 1350 to 1470.}}<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=9}}</ref>
# Independently; viewed without relation to other things or factors. {{defdate|First attested around 1350 to 1470.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{lb|en|grammar}} In a manner that does not take an [[object]].

====Usage notes====
* ''Absolutely'' is not to be confused with [[intensive]]s such as ''very'' or ''indeed'', as it is an unconditional term.

